\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9725236095864781, \"rank\": 0.028251604382701523, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}, {\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_kayak\", \"score\": 0.9969371819570906, \"rank\": 0.003066964221745884, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_kayak\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's hardly surprising that Jessica and Noemie\\u00a0have developed into world-class, Olympic-winning athletes as both their parents were also stars of the canoeing world.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9725236095864781, \"rank\": 0.028251604382701523, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mum Myriam Fox-Jerusalmi competed at the international level from 1979 to 1996 and won bronze in the K1 at the Atlanta Olympics in 1996.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 628, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myriam_Montemayor_Cruz\", \"score\": 0.9999999947590368, \"rank\": 2.222537480034133e-09, \"text\": \"Myriam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myriam_Montemayor_Cruz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myriam_Montemayor_Cruz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French star also won ten medals at the ICF Canoe Slalom World Championships and the World Cup title three consecutive times between 1989 and 1991.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9181206328345846, \"rank\": 0.06216483338183598, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dad Richard, meanwhile, competed for Great Britain for the best part of two decades, winning ten gold medals at the World Championships.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\", \"score\": 0.999900327728661, \"rank\": 9.967926884965442e-05, \"text\": \"Dad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\"}, {\"begin\": 951, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9907383322753363, \"rank\": 0.008646721762699771, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Richard is the only family member without an Olympic medal, having finished fourth and narrowly missing out on silverware in the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"score\": 0.67005149392478, \"rank\": 0.4924223378429582, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to Australian TV following sister Noemie's\\u00a0Olympic gold, Jessica poked fun at her dad's misfortunate, saying: 'It means that poor dad is the only one without an Olympic medal!\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9924657838616695, \"rank\": 0.007133952469349541, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9725236095864781, \"rank\": 0.028251604382701523, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'What a moment for our family.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a moment for these games.'\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 24 hours after the dig, Jessica issued a public apology to her dad, insisting he should proud of his 'great resume' despite his Olympic disappointment.\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9725236095864781, \"rank\": 0.028251604382701523, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I was pretty savage in my interview, and I realised after that was really mean,' she told Australian broadcaster Channel Nine.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9924657838616695, \"rank\": 0.007133952469349541, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia